refactor: Simplify notification components in RightSidebar and enhance task/phase notification display

feat: Implement notifications system with WebSocket support Fact & end task
- Created Notification and NotificationPreference models in the notifications app. - Added serializers and views for handling notifications via REST API. - Integrated WebSocket notifications for real-time updates in the frontend. - Updated RightSidebar component to manage and display notifications. - Implemented signal handlers to create default notification preferences for new users. - Added migration files for the new notifications models and removed old models from websockethandlers. - Enhanced notification display with structured information and improved user experience.

Add WebSocket user status updates in RightSidebar
Implemented WebSocket onmessage handler to update user online status in real-time. Updated UI to use the new is_connected property for displaying user status.

- Updated frontend to establish WebSocket connection for online status. - Removed unused utils app and its related code. - Added is_connected field to ProfileUser model to track user connection status. - Created migrations for new fields and models.
